+++</md></sn><sn><md>### Net Reaction of **Acetyl Co-A Formation**

(From one molecule of pyruvate)

$$
\text{Pyruvate} + \text{NAD}^+ + \text{CoA}
;\longrightarrow;
\text{Acetyl–CoA} + \text{NADH} + \text{H}^+ + \text{CO}_2
$$

#### Key Points

* Occurs in **mitochondrial matrix**
* Produces: **1 NADH**, **1 CO₂**
* Prepares pyruvate for the Krebs cycle

---

### Net Reaction of **Krebs Cycle**

(For one Acetyl Co-A)

$$
\text{Acetyl–CoA} + 3\text{NAD}^+ + \text{FAD} + \text{ADP} + \text{Pi} + 2\text{H}_2\text{O}
;\longrightarrow;
2\text{CO}_2 + 3\text{NADH} + 3\text{H}^+ + \text{FADH}_2 + \text{ATP} + \text{CoA}
$$

#### Key Points

* Produces: **3 NADH**, **1 FADH₂**, **1 ATP (or GTP)**
* Releases: **2 CO₂**
* Regenerates **Oxaloacetate**
* Must run **twice per glucose** (because glucose → 2 pyruvate → 2 Acetyl Co-A)
